name: St Ann's Allotments Orchard
short_description: Heritage fruit trees in a historic site.
description: Located within the oldest and largest Victorian detached allotments in the UK. Public edges feature apples and pears.

name: Sherwood Forest Acorns & Hazels
description: Ancient woodland offering hazelnuts and sweet chestnuts. Focus on the paths near Edwinstowe.

name: River Trent Wild Garlic
description: The damp, shaded banks of the Trent near Victoria Embankment are a carpet of wild garlic in spring.

name: Incredible Edible Beeston
description: Volunteer-maintained planters offering free herbs and seasonal vegetables for commuters.

name: Colwick Country Park Berries
description: Massive yields of blackberries can be found around the perimeter of the main lake.

name: Arkwright Meadows Orchard
description: A community garden with public fruit trees, including plums and local apple varieties.

name: Wollaton Park Chestnuts
description: Large, mature sweet chestnut trees are found in the parkland area away from the main deer herds.

name: Beeston Canal Path Elder
description: Heavy growth of elder bushes along the canal towpath between Beeston and Lenton.

name: Forest Recreation Ground Sloes
description: Blackthorn bushes can be found in the scrubby edges near the tram line.

name: Bestwood Country Park Walnuts
short_description: Former coal mine turned walnut spot.
description: Occasional walnut trees found in the mixed woodland of this large country park.

name: Incredible Edible Nottingham City Centre
description: Public planters integrated into the new green spaces, featuring edible herbs and flowers.

name: Highfields Park Rosehips
description: Abundant wild rosehips found in the lakeside shrubbery and woodland edges.

name: Gedling Country Park Fruit Trail
description: Part of the restoration of the former colliery, featuring various young fruit trees.

name: Nottingham Canal Samphire (Inland)
description: Inland 'coastal' alternative: Wild celery and fennel found along the industrial canal banks.

name: Broxtowe Country Park Hazels
description: Dense areas of hazel can be found in the wooded sections of the park near the M1.
